<br>
Thoric makes an important point here.  One that has been implied but not said directly.  When putting together a guild primarily for raiding purposes, currently you will have a number of Warriors.  Only one will be the main tank, but if he drops you want some back up.  So perhaps you take 4 or 6 Warriors with you, if you have them.<br>
<br>
If Warriors are no longer the main tank of choice, for whatever reason, do you want 6 characters that do similar damage to a Paladin but require their own healers in any situation where they might take some colateral damage?  Or would you fill their slots with Paladins?  Or, if you felt you had plenty of Paladins, wouldn't you fill their slots with Rogues?  Get the point?  With nothing to add but damage, the damage a Warrior brings isn't enough to justify their participation. <br>
<br>
Do you take Paladins on a raid because of their uber damage output?  No, you take them for brells and their various heals, their damage output is a bonus.  Do you take a Warrior on a raid for their uber damage output?  No, you take them for their ability to tank, their damage output is a bonus.  Take away a Paladin's heals, and he won't be wanted on a raid.  Take away a Warrior's tanking advantage and he won't be wanted on a raid.<br>
<br>
Hell, if I was setting up a raid and Paladins and Monks tanked as well as a Warrior, I'd bring nothing but Paladins and Monks because of the heals, buffs, damage output, and FD pulling.  And I would fill any left over melee slots with Rogues and maybe a couple of Rangers.<br>
<br>
And the tanking advantage for Warriors has eroded.  That is a fact. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/02 7:42:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=585>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thoric</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm sorry to be blunt, but at 52, you simply don't have the experience necessary to contribute to the discussion about balance at the end game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
