<br>
Here is the premise.  The Warriors are NOT main tanking at all.  None of them.  Not a single one.  Because it has been determined that a Paladin or Monk can take the damage within an acceptable margin and hold better agro.  So your tanking line up consists completely of Paladins and Monks.  This is the hypothetical scenario.<br>
<br>
If Warriors are completely and utterly NOT your first choice, for tanking the boss mob, does their DPS justify their participation?  Think about it.  All the tanking will be done by Paladins and Monks.  If you are talking damage output, wouldn't those Warriors, who AREN'T in the MT rotation, be better off as Rogues?<br>
<br>
There are four factors to a successful raid, for the most part.  DPS, healing power, debuffs and damage absorbtion.  You pack your ranks with the best of each you can find, as a rule.  For healing power you take Clerics.  For damage absorbtion, currently you take Warriors.  For DPS you take Wizards, Rogues, Monks, Rangers.  You throw in a few Paladins for the combined value of their DPS and their healing power.  You throw in a few secondary healers.  You take Shamen and Enchanters for their debuffs.  You take a couple of each of the other classes to contribute those things unique and desirable from their class.  You've got a raid force.<br>
<br>
Neither Warriors nor Paladins are on a raid because of their outstanding DPS.  The Paladins are their for their DPS, their Heals, and ability to tank when needed.  Warriors are there for the ability to tank and their DPS.  Take away the Warrior's tanking and his DPS alone is jack.  Get Rogues instead.  Replace ALL the Warriors with Rogues.  Get it?<br>
<br>
The only reason you take more than one Warrior on a raid now is because there is a chance the MT might drop.  Not because their DPS is that attractive.  If the class of Warriors aren't MTing, YOU DON'T WANT THEM.  At least not from an efficiency stand point.<br>
