<br>
Somebody needs to put the screws to the rogues, I think.<br>
<br>
For those of you who don't remember, the &quot;Holy Trinity&quot; was the concept that the core of a raid only needed to consist of Clerics, Warriors, and Rogues.  Clerics to heal the Main tanking Warriors, and Rogues to do damage.  Sure, sure, a shaman is nice to slow, an enchanter to buff, a druid (or two) to port, one mage to DS the main tanks and make mod rods (before FT items), a monk to pull, etc etc.  But really, any more than one of those extras is just creating extra lag, so make sure we don't have more than one Wiz, mage, druid, chanter, shaman, etc.<br>
<br>
My point is, sometimes the Holy Trinity demands a knight class to main tank.  I would guess that in anything other than a top-level end-game guild, the Trinity still requires a warrior to tank.  /shrug   If you find that unreasonable, I don't think we're ever going to agree on the subject.<br>
