And the talk of it being a &quot;high end game&quot; issue is crap.  It is an issue for warriors of all levels.  Since I hit 50 it has been even more noticeable.  <br>
<br>
Everyone chose the class they play, it didn't choose them.   I chose warrior because it was what I wanted.  I knew I wouldn't be able to solo effectively, but that was something I could give up.  I knew I wouldn't be able to cast spells to help with damage, heals, etc.  That is what I chose to give up to be the best at what I do.  After the paladin upgrades, what has the class actually given up?  Lower skill caps? Slightly.  Lower hps, armor class, mitigation, weapons?  PFFT!  Like I said in an earlier post.  It seems to me that the only argument against necessary warrior upgrades are coming from paladins who want to be warriors with spells.  I'm sorry if that offends some people, but that is absolutely all I have seen.  Pallies already make great tanks, and I'm happy that they do.  But you shouldn't be able to touch a warrior at it.  That is the price all warriors have paid for their class, and to marginalize it by saying that an upgrade shouldnt happen because you want to tank as well as a warrior is ridiculous. That is the price you paid when you chose your class.<br>
<br>
Ragingwolf Fyreborne<br>
Black Thorn<br>
Bristlebane<br>
<br>
